title: solo thinking v. information consumption
pid: 08dc2cef-0fdd-418c-8bee-4a4594d188a0
body: |2-
  We dislike the urge to surf (too excess) as an anonymous reader|listener|viewer.
  Doing one's own thinking is (the?) natural diametrically-opposed alternative.
  A healthy life balances both -- one *should* (for instance) read others' work,
  but one should also think for oneself.
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
